description:
Fix the wrong Keycloak realm in the CMS Admin SPA OIDC service.

**File to edit:** cms-admin-react/src/services/oidc.ts

**Current (wrong) values on lines 4-7:**
```ts
const KEYCLOAK_AUTH_ENDPOINT = import.meta.env.VITE_KEYCLOAK_AUTH_ENDPOINT || 'https://keycloak.localhost:8443/realms/auth-sandbox/protocol/openid-connect/auth';
const KEYCLOAK_LOGOUT_ENDPOINT = import.meta.env.VITE_KEYCLOAK_LOGOUT_ENDPOINT || 'https://keycloak.localhost:8443/realms/auth-sandbox/protocol/openid-connect/logout';
const CLIENT_ID = import.meta.env.VITE_CLIENT_ID || 'cms-client';
const REDIRECT_URI = import.meta.env.VITE_REDIRECT_URI || 'https://cms.localhost:8443/cms-admin/';
```

**Expected (correct) values:**
```ts
const KEYCLOAK_AUTH_ENDPOINT = import.meta.env.VITE_KEYCLOAK_AUTH_ENDPOINT || 'https://keycloak.localhost:8443/realms/admin-sandbox/protocol/openid-connect/auth';
const KEYCLOAK_LOGOUT_ENDPOINT = import.meta.env.VITE_KEYCLOAK_LOGOUT_ENDPOINT || 'https://keycloak.localhost:8443/realms/admin-sandbox/protocol/openid-connect/logout';
const CLIENT_ID = import.meta.env.VITE_CLIENT_ID || 'cms-admin-client';
const REDIRECT_URI = import.meta.env.VITE_REDIRECT_URI || 'https://cms.localhost:8443/cms-admin/';
```

**Why:** The CMS Admin page should be protected by the admin-sandbox realm (same as admin-mock-react), NOT the auth-sandbox realm which is for content pages. The CLIENT_ID must match a client registered in the admin-sandbox realm.

**Reference:** See admin-mock-react/src/services/oidc.ts for the correct pattern using admin-sandbox realm and 'admin-client'.

**After the change:** Run `npm run build` (or `bun run build`) inside cms-admin-react/ to rebuild the dist. Verify the dist/index.html loads and the built JS references the admin-sandbox realm.

Magic string "2" at AuthService.java:105:
  String assertionToken = jwtService.issueKeycloakAssertionToken(device.getUserId(), "2");

extract to constant: private static final String ACR_BIOMETRIC = "2";
